The course gives an understanding of the broader management information systems in use today. Students will develop an understanding of the applications of information management to accounting data and have an overview of the accounting software selection criteria.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course is intended to provide students with knowledge, which they can apply in the design and implementation of accounting information systems. Students who have passed the course have basic knowledge what are the basic criteria in choosing accounting software.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  As a result of the course the student: 1)	has an overview about various accounting and enterprise resource planning (ERP) software and can compare their functionality, 2)	has basic knowledge about the accounting software selection criteria.
